cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on generating narrative stories about visual scenes using AI, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its intersection with computer science. The second likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image and video analysis. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms and models that can learn from data. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval of relevant information from large collections of data, which is relevant for generating stories from image sequences.
